[Bioterrorism or the more trendy agroterrorism, is certainly one
possibility accounting for the 2 FMD virus identifications recently
obtained from the Mercosur countries. The 28 infected animals in Brazil did
show clinical signs. The virus type was O. It is important to remember that
the cattle in Argentina never had clinical signs and were only
serologically positive to A24. Furthermore, our first reports were that
Brazil and Argentina had banned animal related commerce with Paraguay. We
have no good information yet on the virus type and clinical condition of
animals in Paraguay. Good explanations for what is going on are in short
supply and in such an environment, some may leap to agroterrorism as an
explanation. Let's look first and await the results of the Brazilian
investigation. - Mod.PC
